    Saruman, Keeper of Isengard x 4<br>
    Orthanc Berserker x 2<br>
    <a href="javascript:card_browser(39)">Troop of Uruk-hai</a> x 4<br>
    <a href="javascript:card_browser(24)">Lurtz, Servant of Isengard</a>    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> The base of this deck is cycling. It can Setup very fast, and can win with one side or the other.<br>
<br>
Sites:<br>
Well, these are very simple:<br>
2,4 and 9 for uruks.<br>
1 because if Shards, Aragorn or Boromir don´t show up early (it didnt´happen to me, but can happen) you will be hand clogged. <br>
3 you start with two elves, since it has not burden removal, its the best site.<br>
6,7 (and maybe 8) anti-swarm (or Moria stoping you at your own 8!)<br>
<br>
Fellowship:<br>
Bid low, since the deck doesn´t have BR. I usually bid 1, my girlfriend 2... <br>
Since the strenght of the deck depends on cycling you need a soon as posible a man or Shards. If the opponent Starts with other than Pony and you doesn´t have a man or shards in your hand, go and take a mulligan! That rule is very good for the shadow player because if they double move you reconcile your hand twice before your fellowship phase.<br>
Besides that the strategy is easy drop anithing you can´t play or dont want to play to the shards, use elrond to draw cards, set your fellowship and go! nobody can stop you!.<br>
The name for the deck  comes because sometimes the fellowship doesn´t set up quickly and you don´t want a 5th companion in play because the uruks and STMTN will hurt you in the early game, so boromir (or aragorn in desesperate cases) goes to the Shards and waits there with all his equipment to the late game, when he is a game winner whith horn. I even won games without the help of Boromir, who was seeing from his home, the shards,   how frodo survived site 9.<br>
And Filbert Bolger is the best ally in site 9!!!<br>
<br>
Shadow:<br>
More or less Standard Uruks. The deck has a lot of pumps and the Battle cry can take a companion without warning from sting. Saruman is da Man!!!<br>
2 Saruman Power, because the nasty trust me/ betrayal decks, and for the &quot;mirror match&quot; (Denial is a hard match for uruks in the early game).<br>
2 Uruk Raiders because they are cheap and extremely good against Horn decks.<br>
Abandoning Reason for Madnees may be a game-winner in late sites.<br>
<br>
The ¿Why?´s section:<br>
¿Why not Pathfinder?<br>
With the shards could be a great card for site 7, but I really don´t depend TOO much on allies. 3 times I have been confluenced, 3 of that I have win.<br>
<br>
¿Why Orthanc Berserkers whith no CYPFY?<br>
Because these days, Starting with Anti-Euro Meta from Patrick &quot;CaptCanada&quot; Malboeuf, the people are relaying less on Aragorn, but the berserker is a good 11 strenght minion, that can be pumped to the overwhelm limit.<br>
<br>
Posible Changes to the deck:<br>
Can you Protect Me from yourself is a great card with the Orthanc Berserker, but only in Strong Aragorn Meta. (maybe out: Abandoning RfM or the Warriors or Riders)<br>
Get out Filibert since you have only one hobbit, but he is surely a game winner, and beer giver! (maybe out 1 Uruk Warrior)<br>
Maybe a Pathfinder for the site 7, because the deck has Shards, it doesn´t clog your hand (but i didn´t want to make the deck bigger)<br>
<br>
Thanks to section:<br>
To my girlfriend Prix, who made this deck with me<br>
